“WWG1WGA” Apr 13 2018. Use takes over for long form. 6-8 mentions per month Apr – Sep 2018. Only 2 uses in Oct 2018, but big spike in Nov 2018 already.
“Trust the plan” Feb 5 2018. Common usage at first, high of 11 mentions in May 2018, single mention monthly Jun, Aug, Sep. Last seen Sep 5 2018.
“Where we go one, we go all” Jan 8 2018. Five uses in Jan 2018, slowing to two-three mentions per month through May 2018, single use Aug, Sep, Oct, Nov. Gradually replaced by short form WWG1WGA.
“Tick Tock” Dec 10 2017. Last seen Apr 20 2018. Surprisingly Q only uses the phrase 3 times. His followers ran with it though.
“Be the autists we know you are” Dec 9 2017. Phrase used only 3 times, last seen Feb 15 2018. “Autists” as reference to followers has appeared roughly twice a month ever since.

“Future answers past” Nov 23 2017. Only time it’s used.
“Future proves past” Nov 24 2017 takes over the next day. Half dozen mentions every month until May 2018, then slowing suddenly to two mentions in June 2018, one in July 2018. No mentions again until Nov 7 2018.
“Do you believe in coincidences?” Nov 6 2017. Fairly constant, usage has stayed high (roughly 6 mentions per month) ever since.
“Jason Bourne (CIA/Dream)” Nov 11 2017. Total five mentions in Nov 2017, last seen Nov 20 2017.

“Iron Eagle” Nov 9 2017 First post after Q is given a designated handle. Common in Nov 2017, slowing to one post per month Jan-Apr 2018, when it is not mentioned again until Aug 11, which is the last occurrence.
"Godfather III" Nov 5 2017. Last seen Dec 9 2017.
"Snow White" Nov 4 2017. Common through November, one post December 15 2017, one post January 21 2018. Last seen Aug 30 2018.
"Wizards & Warlocks" Oct 31 2017 in passing (as “wizards and warlocks (inside term)”). First standalone mention Nov 3 2017. Last seen Feb 10 2018.

"Alice & Wonderland" Nov 2 2017. Mentioned across dozens of drops initially, lasted only 2 days until Q just came out and told followers Hilary Clinton was Alice and Saudi Arabia was Wonderland on Nov 4 2017. Last seen Dec 22 2017.
"Calm before the storm" Nov 2 2017. Last seen Nov 24 2017. Four mentions of “the Storm” scattered in 2018, last seen Sep 21 2018.
“Enjoy the show” used in passing Oct 29 2017 (“sit back and enjoy the show”). First standalone mention Dec 10 2017. Has been common ever since, almost always to end a drop.

"The Great Awakening" Oct 29 2017 in passing, first standalone mention Nov 4 2017. Common throughout Nov and Dec 2017, then slowing to roughly one mention per month through 2018. Last seen Aug 21 2018.
